2. GitHub / Portfolio README (detailed)
Project Name: Video Uploader API
Description:

This is a mini SaaS-like backend service for uploading, managing, and serving video files. Built with Django and Django REST Framework (DRF), it demonstrates professional backend skills and REST API design.

Key Features:

CRUD operations: Create, Read, Update, Delete videos

File uploads & media serving: Store and serve video files securely

Pagination: Efficiently handle large video lists

JWT Authentication: User-specific access control (coming soon)

Expandable: Can be extended into a full SaaS platform with user dashboards, subscriptions, or analytics

Tech Stack:

Python 3.x, Django 5.x, Django REST Framework

SQLite (or other DBs)

JWT for authentication

Optional: Frontend can consume the API

Why it’s a strong backend project:

Demonstrates professional REST API development

Handles real-world scenarios like file uploads and user-specific data

Can be deployed online and extended to a full SaaS product






✅ Best way to describe it

On GitHub / portfolio:

“Mini SaaS-like backend app for uploading and managing videos”

If emphasizing functionality:

“Video uploader tool with REST API, CRUD, and file storage”



